Education
Istanbul Technical University (4/4) Expected June 2026
BSc, Electronics and Communication Engineering, GPA: 3.01/4 Istanbul, Turkey
• Relevant Coursework: Data Structures and Algorithms (C++), Prob & Stat (Python), Signal Processing, Linear Algebra,
Numerical Methods (Python), Quantum Computing (Qiskit), Intro. to Optimization, ANNs, Machine Learning
Experience
Turkcell Aug 2025 – Sep 2025
Radio Network Intern Istanbul
• During my internship at Turkcell Radio Network Department, I worked on LTE/4G, 5G NR and wireless access
technologies.

I took part in:
* analyzing 4G/5G radio interfaces, resource grids, control channels, and MIMO structures,
* examining key radio KPIs (RSRP/RSRQ, SINR, throughput, PRB usage) and their impact on coverage and
capacity,
* studying Superbox (FWA) performance, cell selection logic, and customer-side signal quality behavior,
* visiting the captive office and examining real base station hardware and RAN equipment,
* attending a technical session hosted by Huawei engineers on 5G RAN architecture and beamforming. Baykar Technologies June 2025 – Aug 2025
Artificial Intelligence Intern Istanbul
• I worked on artificial intelligence software for the best unmanned aerial vehicles in their field around the world. Due
to confidentiality agreements, I cannot mention my work. In general, I worked on Monte Carlo simulations,
uncertainty estimation, and reinforcement learning.

Eurasia Institute of Earth Sciences Mar 2024 – June 2025
Research Intern Istanbul
• Under the supervision of Prof. Dr. Oguz H. G ˘ o¨g˘us¸¨ , I conducted research on topics such as earthquake prediction
using AI and predicting optimal points for extracting underground thermal waters. As part of this work, I was
awarded a scholarship from TUB¨ ˙ITAK. I applied to present a poster at the EGU2026 (Vienna). Additionally, I had the
opportunity to work within a large and international team of researchers. ITU ATA Team Sep 2022 – June 2023
Software Team Member Istanbul
• Me and my teammates developed unmanned aerial vehicles (UAV) and drones. We came 3rd in the (Teknofest
Competition(10.000+)) and became champions in the (IMechE UAS Challenge).

I took part in:
* the development of the ground control station interface with PyQt,
* the development of autonomous take-off and driving with the help of MissionPlanner and Python Dronekit,
* the development of algorithms and databases for autonomous tracking (97.2% (Yolo and TensorRT) accurasy
rate in foreign drone recognition). Volunteering
ITU ACM Student Chapter June 2022 – Present
Vice President of Technical Affairs Istanbul
• I was the manager of the AlgoComp competition, which attracted more than 1300 participants and helped manage a
budget of 70,000TL (2,400USD). (algocomp.ituacm.com)
• We organized 200+ hours and 10+ trainings on 10+ different topics with our volunteer trainers in the club. (ituacm.com)
• I took part as a trainer in 2 of these trainings (Python / DataScience and ML). (yt/@ituacmsc) (github/@ituacm)
• I was the founding president of DataTeam.

We developed countless open source projects and provided mentoring
support to new participants. Projects
British Airlines Customer Reviews Analysis [Github] | Python, BeautifulSoup, NumPy&Pandas, Matplotlib, Tensorflow, SciKit
Statistical Earthquake Analysis and Clustering [Github] | [App] | Python, Streamlit, NumPy&Pandas, Matplotlib, SciKit
Architectural Style Classification with Artificial Intelligence [Github] | Python, Matlab, Matplotlib, Tensorflow, ResNet50
Scholarships & Awards
